<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[227,341,1741,1767]" box="[227,341,1741,1767]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,341,1741,1767]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,341,1741,1767]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[226,1438,1787,2063]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
The 
<typeStatus box="[283,386,1787,1813]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">holotype</typeStatus>
was deposited in the Museu Paraense Emílio Goeldi but has been on loan since 2004 (O.T. Silveira, pers. comm., 2022). Therefore, we could not examine the 
<typeStatus box="[1098,1201,1823,1849]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">holotype</typeStatus>
except for the lowresolution picture available in Zompro (2004b). According to Zompro (2004b), this species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ghirotto &amp; Crispino &amp; Engelking &amp; Neves &amp; Góis &amp; Chiquetto-Machado" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Caudell" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[351,538,1894,1920]" class="Insecta" genus="Arumatia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubia" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[351,538,1894,1920]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Arumatia dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[545,766,1894,1921]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with which it shares the median segment as long as the metanotum, and the very elongate cerci and basitarsi, traits that can be confirmed from the 
<typeStatus box="[1335,1438,1929,1955]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">holotype</typeStatus>
picture. According to Zompro’s (2004b) description and diagnosis, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ghirotto &amp; Crispino &amp; Engelking &amp; Neves &amp; Góis &amp; Chiquetto-Machado" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Ghirotto &amp; Crispino &amp; Engelking &amp; Neves &amp; Góis &amp; Chiquetto-Machado" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[1015,1132,1965,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Phasmatidae" genus="Echetlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phasmida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgens" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1015,1132,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">A. fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1139,1354,1965,1992]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ghirotto &amp; Crispino &amp; Engelking &amp; Neves &amp; Góis &amp; Chiquetto-Machado" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Caudell" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[290,389,2000,2027]" class="Insecta" genus="Arumatia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis box="[290,389,2000,2027]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">A. dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the stouter body and the longer subgenital plate reaching the end of tergum X, features that are not visible in the picture. However, both in the description and in the picture, a striking feature
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[226,1438,303,526]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
is the much longer cerci than that of other species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ghirotto" authorityName="Ghirotto &amp; Crispino &amp; Engelking &amp; Neves &amp; Góis &amp; Chiquetto-Machado" authorityYear="2022" box="[836,1052,303,329]" class="Insecta" genus="Arumatia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[836,947,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Arumatia</emphasis>
Ghirotto
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1058,1164,303,329]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in comparison with the last terga. Zompro (2004b) also pointed out the black longitudinal dorsal line on the body as a diagnostic feature of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ghirotto &amp; Crispino &amp; Engelking &amp; Neves &amp; Góis &amp; Chiquetto-Machado" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Ghirotto &amp; Crispino &amp; Engelking &amp; Neves &amp; Góis &amp; Chiquetto-Machado" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[353,471,381,408]" class="Insecta" family="Phasmatidae" genus="Echetlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phasmida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis box="[353,471,381,408]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the female 
<typeStatus box="[669,772,381,407]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ghirotto &amp; Crispino &amp; Engelking &amp; Neves &amp; Góis &amp; Chiquetto-Machado, 2022" authorityName="Ghirotto &amp; Crispino &amp; Engelking &amp; Neves &amp; Góis &amp; Chiquetto-Machado" authorityYear="2022" box="[817,957,382,408]" class="Insecta" genus="Arumatia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aramatia" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[817,957,382,408]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. aramatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[966,1148,382,408]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and some specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ghirotto &amp; Crispino &amp; Engelking &amp; Neves &amp; Góis &amp; Chiquetto-Machado" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Caudell" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[229,328,420,447]" class="Insecta" genus="Arumatia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis box="[229,328,420,447]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also present such a line or similar longitudinal markings (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1164,420,447]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[227,270,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,880,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-308@23.[227,1437,878,1847]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 13. Colour variation of Arumatia dubia (Caudell, 1904) gen. et comb. nov., showing metathorax and median segment of females. A–B. ♀ (MZUSP V0561) from Ibaté when nymph (A) or adult (B); C–E. Adult ♀♀ from Ibaté (C: MZUSP V0542, D: MZUSP V0558, E: MZUSP V0560). F–H. Adult (F) and subadult (G–H) ♀♀ from Chapadão do Sul (F: MZUSP V0563, G: MZUSP V0564, H: MZUSP V0565). I–J. Adult ♀♀ from Araguari (I: MZUSP V0547, J: MZUSP V0676). Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6798498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6798498/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs 13A, F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1177,1210,420,447]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="43.[229,272,2000,2026]" captionTargetBox="[262,1346,688,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-136@43.[227,1437,688,1948]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Fig. 25. Arumatia aramatia Ghirotto gen. et sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MZUSP 1352). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. Scale bar: 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6798526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6798526/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">25</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ghirotto &amp; Crispino &amp; Engelking &amp; Neves &amp; Góis &amp; Chiquetto-Machado" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Zompro" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[1233,1438,420,447]" class="Insecta" genus="Arumatia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis box="[1233,1438,420,447]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Arumatia fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from the seasonal forest of the Cerrado in Estação Ecológica Serra das Araras near Barra do Bugres, 
<collectingRegion box="[324,541,499,525]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Mato Grosso state</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[552,624,499,525]" name="Brazil" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[640,728,499,526]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="76.[227,270,1776,1802]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,873,1745]" captionTargetId="figure-280@76.[227,1437,873,1745]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Fig. 52. Distribution map of species of Arumatia Ghirotto gen. nov. in central South America. Brazil is further divided into states which are shown in a thinner line. Note that grey dotted circles represent photographic records of Arumatia dubia gen. et comb. nov. from the iNaturalist (iNat) online platform, the black shield represents an unidentified nymph of Arumatia gen. nov. from MZUSP collection and the grey dotted shields represent photographic records of a potentially new species from iNaturalist." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795726/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
